==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rack-rent
<hw>Rack"-rent`</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧k"r⟦ecr⟧nt`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
rent of the full annual value of the tenement, or near it; an excessive
or unreasonably high rent.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rack-rent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rack-rent
<hw>Rack"-rent`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To subject to rack-rent, as
a farm or tenant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rack-renter</ent>⟦br⟧
